task.summary: 不再删除冗余模组文件，而是移动到新文件夹

Refactor RPC handling and improve cheat detection logic
Replaced direct method patching with a dynamic `TargetMethods` approach for broader compatibility and updated player association logic. Made cheat data handling methods private to encapsulate functionality and prevent external access while refining position and ban processing logic.

Refactor RPC handling and enhance cheat detection logic
Reorganized RPC processing into modular methods for better readability and maintainability. Improved cheat detection by adding overload protection and additional player data checks. Updated vent handling to include new role types and enhanced player data management with better state tracking.

Update RPC method and remove obsolete patch
Replace `StartRpc` with `StartRpcImmediately` for better performance and remove the deprecated `StartRpcPatch` class. Additionally, update the `AmongUs.GameLibs.Steam` package to the latest version (2025.4.15) for improved compatibility.

Update RPC name formatting and adjust list index removal
Replaced the invalid RPC name format with a more concise representation and corrected the index in the list removal logic to ensure proper functionality when `allowDesktop` is false and the user is a debugger. These changes improve code clarity and fix potential indexing issues.

Refactor and enhance mod announcement loading logic
Moved announcement loading to a separate thread and added Harmony patches to control popup behavior. This ensures announcements are only shown after loading is complete and improves the user experience by re-showing the popup post-load.

Rename patch methods for clarity and consistency
Renamed `A` to `AnnouncementPopupPrefix` and `B` to `AnnouncementPopupPostfix` to better reflect their purpose and improve code readability. This change aligns method names with their roles in Harmony patching.
